head_commit.message:
fix(ci): resolve all CI failures on docs/normalize-file-naming

- ESLint: add security/detect-unsafe-regex disable comments in pii-scrubber.ts and ai.langgraph.workflow.spec.ts
- ESLint: rename unused 'state' to '_state' in course-generator.workflow.ts
- ESLint: remove unused 'sql' import from announcements.service.ts
- ESLint: rename unused 'closeAllPools' to '_closeAllPools' in crm.service.spec.ts
- test.yml: build @edusphere/nats-client, auth, config, metrics before integration/graphql tests
- metrics: exclude src/nestjs.*.ts from vitest coverage thresholds
- docker-build.yml: change PNPM_VERSION from 9 to 10 (lockfile format compatibility)
- subgraph-core: add @edusphere/nats-client and nats deps for CRM NATS consumer
- db: exclude seed/migrate files from TypeScript compilation
- playwright: update E2E port to 5175, disable server reuse for clean test runs

Co-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>

workflow_runs.name: PR Quality Gate
workflow_runs.display_title: feat: Admin Upgrade F-101-F-113 + Tier3 (39 features) + CI + Codegen fix

head_commit.message:
fix(gateway): commit @graphql-hive/cli devDependency to align with lockfile

The pnpm-lock.yaml in the previous commit included @graphql-hive/cli for
the gateway package (added while locally testing schema:check/publish
scripts) but apps/gateway/package.json was never staged for that commit.
This caused `pnpm install --frozen-lockfile` to fail on every CI job with
a lockfile integrity error.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
